Collapse multiple rows to a single value

Collapse multiple rows to a single value

# S3 method for tbl_ts
summarise(.data, ..., drop = FALSE)

# S3 method for tbl_ts
summarize(.data, ..., drop = FALSE)

Arguments

.data

A tsibble.
...

Name-value pairs of experssions.
drop

FALSE returns a tsibble object as the input. TRUE drops a tsibble and returns a tibble.

Details

Time index will not be collapsed by summarise.tbl_ts.

See also

dplyr::summarise

dplyr::summarize

Examples

pedestrian %>%
  summarise(Total = sum(Count))
#> # A tsibble: 17,542 x 2 [1HOUR]
#>    Date_Time           Total
#>    <dttm>              <int>
#>  1 2015-01-01 00:00:00  2866
#>  2 2015-01-01 01:00:00  1535
#>  3 2015-01-01 02:00:00   994
#>  4 2015-01-01 03:00:00   569
#>  5 2015-01-01 04:00:00   311
#>  6 2015-01-01 05:00:00   159
#>  7 2015-01-01 06:00:00   129
#>  8 2015-01-01 07:00:00   146
#>  9 2015-01-01 08:00:00   258
#> 10 2015-01-01 09:00:00   419
#> # ... with 17,532 more rows
## drop = TRUE ----
pedestrian %>%
  summarise(Total = sum(Count), drop = TRUE)
#> # A tibble: 1 x 1
#>      Total
#>      <int>
#> 1 45494418
